nah.  don't legislate the interest rate.  use free-market rules to
select the interest rate.

Timothy's Futures rules would work for loans: you would sell a Mark
Future which would give you Marks now in exchange for a payment of
(presumably) a large quantity of Marks later.  the effective interest
rate would be determined by the price you could get for the Future.

k.
