I cleaned up some language in this, and made the Interest Rate a 
separate Entity, modifiable elsewhere.

Proto-PROPOSAL DB12 (Vanyel)
Loans
(Creates a Rule)
 
 If a Player believes that e is in need of extra Marks, he may request a
 Loan from the Banker.  The granting of such a loan is at the Banker's
 discretion.  Any money received from such a loan must be paid to the
 Bank, plus the Interest Rate for each day since the loan was first 
 granted.  A loan is not considered to be paid off until all marks have
 been paid back, and all Interest has been paid.  Once a loan is paid off
 the Loanee shall stop daily Interest Payments.

 The Interest Rate shall be specified through NRC Proposal with Adoption
 Factor of 1, or specified in another Rule.  Any specification in the 
 Ruleset overrides any NRC to the contrary.  The Interest Rate may be 
 specified relative to the amount borrowed, or an absolute amount, or
 based on current economy.

[***Again, Kelly, should it be "Adoption Factor" here or something else?]
 
***END PROTO
 
 Revision history:
 first proto 27 Sep 1994 3:45 AM CDT
 second proto 6 Oct 1994 11:35 PM CDT
 
Vanyel

